{
"script": "One summer, a woman stepped into the street and began to dance, and she simply could not stop. Hour after hour, day after day, her feet kept moving until they bled. Then something impossible happened. Her neighbors joined her, one by one, until hundreds were dancing uncontrollably through the town. And this was no celebration. People collapsed from exhaustion, strokes, and heart attacks, dropping dead in the streets. Doctors were baffled, blaming hot blood and prescribing even more dancing. To this day, nobody fully knows why it happened, only that an entire town danced itself into the grave.",
